	<div class=3D"vc_message_box-icon"><i class=3D"fa fa-book"></i>
	</div><p><b>Em</b> definition&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://kyleschaeffer.com/dev=
elopment/css-font-size-em-vs-px-vs-pt-vs/">provided by&nbsp;Kyle Schaeffer<=
/a></p>
<p>The =E2=80=9Cem=E2=80=9D is a scalable unit that is used in web document=
 media. An em is equal to the current font-size, for instance, if the font-=
size of the document is 12pt, 1em is equal to 12pt. Ems are scalable in nat=
ure, so 2em would equal 24pt, 0.5em would equal 6pt, etc. Ems are becoming =
increasingly popular in web documents due to scalability and their mobile-d=
evice-friendly nature.</p>
</div>
<div class=3D"vc_message_box vc_message_box-standard vc_message_box-rounded=
